By the end, Grandmother added cilantro and called it a cousin of chaat. Priya walked away feeling lighter. The day had not become perfect, but it had turned, like a page, toward something kinder. Later, when Priya remembered the moment, the important part was not being brave right away. It was choosing to act while still feeling unsure.$body$,'literary'::map_passage_genre,184,780,'201_210'::map_rit_band,'original',$topic$G4 passage seed 2026-04-30: family food: trying something new$topic$),
(4,$title$The Broken Clay Moon$title$,$body$Diego noticed the problem before anyone said it aloud. In the art room after dismissal, his elbow cracked Hana's clay moon. The room seemed to pause around a silver-painted clay moon, as if even ordinary things were waiting for a choice. A small worry tapped at Diego's thoughts, steady as rain on a window.

