(8,$title$Lemonade in the Wind$title$,$body$Nia noticed the problem before anyone said it aloud. In a windy driveway, her lemonade sign kept falling over. The room seemed to pause around a cardboard sign, as if even ordinary things were waiting for a choice. A small worry tapped at Nia's thoughts, steady as rain on a window.

