(9,$title$Caddo Morning by the River$title$,$body$Soren noticed the problem before anyone said it aloud. In an East Texas village near a river, he wanted to hurry through his basket work. The room seemed to pause around river cane strips, as if even ordinary things were waiting for a choice. A small worry tapped at Soren's thoughts, steady as rain on a window.

